---
import TopicLayout from '../../components/TopicLayout.astro';

const exampleQuestions = [
  'How should a non-technical leader think about AI adoption?',
  'What is the right AI strategy for a mid-size company?',
  'How do I evaluate which tasks to automate with AI first?',
  'What are the biggest mistakes companies make with AI?',
];

const relatedTopics = [
  { title: 'Enterprise AI', href: '/topics/enterprise-ai' },
  { title: 'AI Agents', href: '/topics/ai-agents' },
  { title: 'Context Engineering', href: '/topics/context-engineering' },
  { title: 'Vibe Coding', href: '/topics/vibe-coding' },
];
---

<TopicLayout
  title="AI Strategy"
  metaTitle="AI Strategy for Leaders — AmbitiousOS"
  metaDescription="AI strategy frameworks for business leaders. How to evaluate, adopt, and deploy AI in your organization. Research from Reading Ambitiously."
  headline="AI Strategy for Leaders"
  intro="Most AI strategies fail — not because the technology doesn't work, but because leaders don't have the context to make good decisions. Strategy without understanding is just guessing."
  exampleQuestions={exampleQuestions}
  relatedTopics={relatedTopics}
>
  <p>
    The best AI strategies start with understanding what AI can actually do today — not in theory,
    but in practice. This means understanding the difference between copilots and agents, knowing
    which tasks benefit from automation vs. augmentation, and having a realistic view of implementation
    timelines and costs.
  </p>
  <p>
    AmbitiousOS was built for exactly this use case. Leaders who don't have time to read every AI paper,
    follow every product launch, or attend every conference can instead ask their personal Chief AI
    Officer. The platform synthesizes 64+ editions of curated research into conversational answers
    grounded in real data, real companies, and real outcomes.
  </p>
</TopicLayout>
